Mr. Joseph Akinsanya, the new Unit Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) in Ifo, Ogun, has pledged the unit’s commitment to minimize crashes in the area. Akinsanya made this known in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Friday in Ifo, Ogun. NAN reports that the new unit commander, transferred from Imo, assumed duty on Tuesday (March 9) to replace Mr Joshua Ibitimi. who was redeployed to Lagos State.He said that the unit would improve on its operations and collaborate with other sister agencies to stem road traffic accidents. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! “We intend to be public friendly and increase public enlightenment programmes in Ifo and its environs to educate the people on the importance of safety.” “We will also enforce traffic rules and regulations to ensure sanity as well as reduce mishaps on the highways,” he said. Bandits Attack Federal Forestry College In Kaduna Okowa To Inaugurate Ovwor-Effurun-Otor Bridge March 16 Source (NAN)